      "writtenOn": "2015-11-30T20:21:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "do we guarantee anything regarding thread safety of the API?\ncurrent implementation may easily loose a command and deadlock if several camera_device_*() functions are called in parallel; this code\n\n  qemu_cond_signal(\u0026cts-\u003ecmd_available);\n  while (cts-\u003erdy \u003d\u003d 0) {\n    qemu_cond_wait(\u0026cts-\u003ecmd_ready, \u0026cts-\u003elock);\n  }\n\n... doesn\u0027t guarantee that the handler thread wakes up first, it\u0027s just the most probable outcome. it\u0027s possible that a separate thread calling camera_device_blah() wakes and captures the cts-\u003elock mutex\n\nThe only guaranteed implementations would be either queue of commands or some wait in the beginning of camera_device_*() until the previous existing command is processed",
